{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d856f368-0bcb-41c2-9040-f41f618cecd3","content":"The `src/MyMcpServer/` directory doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n    <!-- Required for dotnet tool packaging -->\n    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n    <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n    <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n    <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n    <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n    <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n    <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key properties:**\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `PackAsTool` | Marks the package as a global/local dotnet tool |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users invoke (e.g., `dotnet tool run my-mcp-server`) |\n| `OutputType=Exe` | Required — tools must be executables |\n\n**Publishing steps:**\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Users install with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nThat's the minimum configuration needed. The `PackAsTool` + `ToolCommandName` combo is what makes it installable as a dotnet tool rather than a plain NuGet library.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6c8bea79-da96-4cc1-8af2-7107c2653403","outputTokens":553,"requestId":"201B:35A1EF:1C35C9E:1F436D9:6A0522B8"},"id":"fa57543d-35e9-4549-84e6-1e5ae872503a","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:17:54.412Z","parentId":"230190b7-7dda-4496-adf1-a2c291f8176b"}
